The Federal Executive Council on Wednesday approved the hiring of a consultant to conduct a study that will aid the implementation of the present administration’s Economic Recovery and Growth Plan.

Minister of Budget and National Planning Udo Udoma told State House correspondents at the end of a meeting of the Council presided over by Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo at the Presidential Villa, Abuja.







ALSO SEE: Thousands of pump-action rifles imported by Kanu — FG

The cost of the approved consultancy job is N458 million.

The consultant would identify relevant stakeholders in both private and public sectors for the implementation of the ERGP in agriculture, transportation, power, gas and processing, among others.







			
